Why worker nodes in private subnet
----------------------------------
âœ… Short interview answer ( realtime)
Worker nodes are placed in private subnets to prevent direct internet access, improve security, and follow enterprise security standards.
EXAMPLE:
--------
User (Internet)
   â†“
Application Load Balancer (Public Subnet)
   â†“
Kubernetes Service / Ingress
   â†“
Worker Nodes (Private Subnet)
   â†“
Pods (Application)
ğŸš« Users never talk directly to worker nodes
--------------------------------------------------
ğŸ”¹ MAIN REASONS (Point-to-Point)
1ï¸âƒ£ Security (MOST IMPORTANT)
If worker nodes are PUBLIC âŒ
Anyone can try:
SSH
Port scanning
Attacks
Node IP is exposed to internet
----------------------------------
If worker nodes are PRIVATE âœ…
No public IP
No direct inbound traffic
Only ALB can reach them
ğŸ“Œ Banking, insurance, fintech â†’ mandatory
------------------------------------------
Best answer:
â€œTechnically yes, but in real-time production we never do that. Worker nodes are always placed in private subnets for security and compliance.â€
